    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Any correction or removal of errors. In techniques such as photogrammetry and aerial photography, rectification refers to compensation for predictably distortive data routinely added to procedures in order to produce correct results.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
